remarks: Amara sp. Strongly punctated elytra. Very flat base of pronotum. Along with two fovea on either side of pronotum. Also has punctuation along edge.
Helluomorphoides sp. Heavily punctated all over. Rufous in color. Long slender elytra with squarish apex.
Helluomorphoides sp. Heavily punctated all over. Rufous in color. Long slender elytra with squarish apex.
slightly larger than AMACON3. Only segments 1 and 2 of antenna rufous. Two slight fovea on pronotum. Pronotum relatively smooth.
Rhadine sp. Shapely pronotum. Punctation around edges of elytra. Entirely rufous in color.
very round pronotum. Defined lines running laterally across pronotum. Two offset setae next to and behind eye. Extra hair on submentum different than Amara sp.
striated elytra. Smooth labrum. Single orbital setae. Slight mentum tooth. Pronotum: largely smooth. Slight medial impression. Hind angle obtuse. Anterior angle sharpish.
pronounced clypeus. Most similar in shape to HARDES. Large amount of punctuation along bottom of pronotum.

Harpalus sp. 90 degree anterior angle that fans out over the elytra. Probably either HAROPA or HARELL.

probably AGOCON. Small species with rounded prototum. Often with rufous pronotum and darker head and elytra. One setae above eye.
